# MangaKids — Project Memory

## What Is This App

MangaKids is an interactive manga/comic app. Users pick an avatar, choose a universe, and an AI-generated branching story unfolds page by page with illustrations. Stories are exported as PDF. The app uses a stars economy for monetisation.

## Monorepo Structure

```
mobile-app/     # React Native (Expo) — the main product
n8n/            # n8n workflows + prompts for AI story generation
  workflows/    # generate-manga-story.json, mangakids-design-system.json
  prompts/      # Example prompts per character/universe
backend/        # (placeholder — Supabase handles backend)
```

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Tech |
|-------|------|
| Framework | Expo 54, React Native 0.81, React 19.1 |
| Routing | expo-router (file-based) |
| State | Zustand (persisted to AsyncStorage, version 4) |
| Backend | Supabase (Auth + PostgreSQL + Storage) |
| Animations | react-native-reanimated 4, lottie-react-native |
| Styling | StyleSheet + theme tokens (`src/theme/theme.ts`) |
| AI Generation | n8n + OpenAI (story JSON) + Google Gemini (images) |
| PDF | expo-print + expo-sharing + expo-file-system |

## Stars Economy (source: `src/constants/stars.ts`)

- **Initial balance:** 6 stars (welcome gift)
- **Costs:** universe unlock = 3, PDF export = 1
- **Rewards:** watch ad = 1, 12h countdown = 1 (no reward on story complete, no daily bonus)
- **Packs (IAP mock):** 10 stars = 2.99 EUR, 25 = 5.99, 60 = 9.99
- **First purchase promo:** small pack gives 20 stars instead of 10
- **Premium lifetime:** 14.99 EUR — unlocks all universes, hides stars badge, no stars needed
- `hasEverPurchased` tracks promo eligibility in store

## Supabase Schema (key tables)

| Table | Purpose | PK type |
|-------|---------|---------|
| `profiles` | Extends auth.users — stars, avatar, unlocked universes, premium | UUID |
| `avatars` | Character frames (normal/blink/wink/happy) + `character_prompt` + `gender` | TEXT |
| `universes` | Story worlds — name, color, emoji, gender, display_order, `avatar_character_names TEXT[]` (links to avatar characters) | TEXT |
| `story_starts` | Opening paragraphs per universe | TEXT |
| `story_paragraphs` | Page content (text + image_url) per universe + page_number | TEXT |
| `narrative_choices` | Branching choices per page — includes `next_page_number` | TEXT |
| `user_story_progress` | Current page per user + universe (upsert) | UUID |
| `user_choices` | Recorded choices for replay/resume | UUID |
| `user_created_stories` | Completed stories (client_id dedup) | UUID |
| `stars_transactions` | Stars audit trail | UUID |

FK note: `avatars.id` and `universes.id` are TEXT, not UUID.

Avatar-Universe relationship: each universe has an `avatar_character_names` TEXT[] column listing which avatar `character_name` values can access it. Universes are fetched via `fetchUniversesByAvatar(avatarCharacterName, gender)` with gender as fallback.

## Auth Flow

1. New user -> onboarding (local only, no Supabase account)
2. Supabase profile created on first star purchase or sign-in
3. Email + password only (Google/Apple SSO hidden for now)
4. Email verification disabled
5. PostgreSQL trigger `handle_new_user` creates profile row on signup
6. Client fallback: `profileService.ensureProfile()` on sign-in if trigger missed
7. `resetStoreForSignOut` clears Zustand + navigates to welcome
8. Dev mode: `_layout.tsx` clears AsyncStorage on every reload

## Navigation Map

```
index.tsx (AuthGate)
  -> /onboarding/welcome -> hero-info -> avatar-select -> /(tabs)/home
  -> /(auth)/login (email sign-in/up) -> ?from=paywall
  -> /(tabs)/home | library | profile
  -> /story/universe-select -> start-select -> generating -> paragraph -> page -> completed
  -> /paywall (modal)
```

## n8n Workflow: generate-manga-story.json

Generates a complete branching manga story:
1. Chat Trigger receives `chatInput`, `characterName` (string), `universeId`
2. Fetches avatar `character_prompt` + `character_trait` + `gender` from Supabase
3. Builds character bible (visual) + character traits (personality) for consistency
4. OpenAI generates story JSON (7 pages: p1a, p1b, p2a, p2b, p3, p4, p5 — 2 paths of 5 pages converging at p3)
5. 2 story_starts = short hook phrases with `first_page_id` (p1a or p1b); pages 1-2 diverge, pages 3-5 converge
6. `character_trait` influences story decisions, reactions, and narrative arc
7. Gemini generates one illustration per page with STRICT character consistency (reinforced prompt)
8. Images uploaded to Supabase Storage (`BD-Pages` bucket)
9. Upserts universe (with `avatar_character_names`), story_starts (with `first_page_id`), story_paragraphs, narrative_choices

## Shared Components (`src/shared/`)

AnimatedPressable, Button, Card, Badge, Avatar, Input, StarsBadge, StarsBadgeWithModal, StarsModal, NotEnoughStarsModal, ErrorFallback, Navbar, ScreenContainer, Loader, LottieAnimation

## Key Patterns

- **AnimatedPressable** wraps all interactive elements (never use `({ pressed }) => ...`)
- **Separate layout + interactive animations:** `entering={}` on outer View, `useAnimatedStyle` on inner View
- **Theme tokens only:** no hardcoded hex, font sizes, spacing, or radii
- **Selector hooks:** prefer `useStars()`, `useHeroProfile()` from `store/selectors.ts`
- **Sync:** `useStoreSync` hook debounces Zustand -> Supabase writes (800ms)
- **French UI** strings, **English** code comments and console.log
